headline: Accenture's AI Upskilling and Restructuring Plan Might Change the Case for Investing in ACN
summary: Accenture recently reported fourth-quarter and full-year fiscal 2025 results, posting US$17.60 billion in Q4 sales and highlighting strong growth in AI-related services, alongside announcing a significant US$865 million restructuring program focused on workforce optimization and AI upskilling. The company simultaneously raised its quarterly dividend by 10.1% and outlined plans for continued share buybacks, underscoring confidence in cash flow generation and its commitment to delivering...

headline: Accenture price target lowered to $285 from $372 at RBC Capital
summary: RBC Capital lowered the firm’s price target on Accenture (ACN) to $285 from $372 but keeps an Outperform rating on the shares. The company delivered solid Q4 results but provided initial FY26 that was mixed vs. prior estimates, which was the main reason for the stock price pressure, the analyst tells investors in a research note.
